					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I could be wrong, but my impression was that Nintendo ditched this design and Sony, so maybe Nintendo also realized that it sucked and intended to release a different CD-ROM system (which obviously was also cancelled).  It's a fascinating bit of history, but seems like an odd choice to want to reproduce.  Sorry I don't have a link for it, but I remember seeing Nintendo docs that were leaked about the CD-ROM system and it didn't look like the discovered Playstation at all.  Much more RAM, 21mhz 32-bit RISC CPU, 65C02.  Seemed like the doc had a decent amount of info (I think it was mostly about the CD-ROM data formats and how to load), but I was a little annoyed that it never said what that 32-bit CPU was exactly.</div>

